<p>
<a name="datta">@HI{{@EM{{hazudatta}}}}</a> is the past form of @HI{{@EM{{hazuda}}}} and indicates what the speaker thinks should have happened.
It is most commonly used when the result turns out to be different from what had been expected.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@FG{{@KJ{{trip^going}}:ryokou}}ni@KJ{{going}}ku@EM{{hazudatta}}. shikashi,@FG{{@KJ{{ill^spirit}}:byouki}}de@KJ{{going}}kenakunatta.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I was supposed to go on a trip. However, I fell ill and couldn't go.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

